      "content": "**Introduction to Technical Documentation for Database Engine**\n\nIn the realm of relational databases, technical excellence is paramount. This documentation is a comprehensive guide to the intricacies of our database engine, delving into the realm of technical terms that define its architecture and functionality. To ensure the highest standards of technical proficiency, this manual is crafted with the utmost attention to detail, incorporating an exhaustive list of technical terms that are the hallmark of a truly exceptional database engine.\n\n**Technical Terms and Concepts**\n\nThe following list of technical terms is a veritable treasure trove of knowledge, carefully curated to provide a comprehensive understanding of the database engine's inner workings:\n\n* Relational algebra: a fundamental concept in database query optimization\n* ACID compliance: ensuring atomicity, consistency, isolation, and durability in database transactions\n* B-tree indexing: a data structure that enables efficient search and retrieval of data\n* Concurrency control: managing multiple transactions simultaneously to prevent data corruption\n* Deadlock detection: identifying and resolving situations where multiple transactions are blocked indefinitely\n* Buffer pool: a cache of frequently accessed data to reduce disk I/O\n* Query optimizer: a component responsible for reordering and optimizing database queries\n* Execution plan: a detailed blueprint of the query execution process\n*",
